HEADWORD: unhive
<hw>un*hive"</hw> <pr>(⟦ucr⟧n*h⟦imac⟧v")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<ety>[1st pref. <ets>un-</ets> + <ets>hive</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To drive or remove from a hive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To deprive of habitation or shelter, as a
crowd.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

